law.text:
The arrest level of the system shall consist of at least the following information:
Name of offender, together with personal identification number (if known);
Arresting agency;
Date, place and time of offense;
Number of arrest charges;
Listing of arrest charges by name, KRS number and citation number;
Charge sequence and incident number;
Level of arrest charged or degree of offense charged;
Date, time, and place of arrest;
If a theft or criminal damage to property offense, the dollar amount of property damaged or stolen;
Exact disposition of the case by police following arrest; and
Date of disposition of the case by the police.
